ACQUISITION: International Business Communications (Holdings) PLC bought Donoghue Organization Inc., publisher of Donoghue's Moneyletter, for $2 million.
William Donoghue, founder and chairman, said the deal includes a five-year agreement -- that will generate at least $1.2 million in payments -- under which he will continue to serve as publisher and marketing spokesman for the Donoghue newsletters. 

